?! The sacrifice is bad enough as it is however even if I do want to sac a piece it should have been the knight that I sacrificed, not the bishop. However the main idea behind the sacrifice was to leave white in a position where it is very difficult to develop and coordinate the pieces, I thought by having my knight on g4 white would have a difficult time however I guess I just got lazy and didn't put enough thought into it. Because white has a reasonably easy game after this.
